## Phase 5 — Production Deployment (Week 12+)

> **Goal:** Deploy as production SaaS

| Component | Platform |
|-----------|----------|
| Frontend | Vercel |
| Backend API | Railway or Render |
| Database | Supabase (already) |
| Docker Execution | AWS EC2 or Fly.io |
| Real-time | Socket.io on backend server |
| CLI | npm registry (`npm install -g collabspace-cli`) |

---

## Recommended Build Order

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Start with **Phase 1** — it has the highest impact with lowest risk. Each phase builds on the previous.

```mermaid
graph TD
  P1[Phase 1: Core Improvements] --> P2[Phase 2: Version Control]
  P2 --> P3[Phase 3: Collaboration]
  P3 --> P4[Phase 4: Advanced]
  P4 --> P5[Phase 5: Deployment]
```

## What to Build First?

I recommend starting with **Phase 1** immediately:
1. **Activity Feed** — makes the dashboard feel alive
2. **File upload/download** — essential for repo UX
3. **README rendering** — makes repos look professional

Then move to **Phase 2** for branching + PRs (the core of version control).

---

## Verification Plan

### Per-Phase Testing
- Unit test each API endpoint
- Browser test each UI feature
- CLI integration tests (init → add → commit → push → pull)

### End-to-End
- Create workspace → create repo → push from CLI → view commits → create branch → PR → merge
- Two users editing same file in real-time
- Role-based access (viewer can't push)
